<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Diagnostic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">The male can be separated from its congeners by its large size combined with unmarked wing; spatulate anal point; superior volsella leaf-shapped; inferior volsella with strong, split setae and digitiform and strongly setose gonostylus.</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1033.60686.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534700" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
