<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Male imago (n = 1).</emphasis>
Total length 4.35 mm. Wing length 1.96 mm. Total length/wing length 2.22. Wing length/length of profemur 2.45.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Colouration</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Thorax and legs brown, abdomen light brown. Wing membrane without dark markings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Antenna</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
AR = 0.16. Thirteenth flagellomere 124 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Temporal setae 6 in single row. Clypeus with 15 setae. Tentorium 113 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, maximum width 25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Stipes not measurable. Palp segment lengths (in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
): 37, 33, 74, 107, 138. Third palpomere with 2 sensilla clavata subapically, longest about 25 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Fifth palpomere/third palpomere 1.86.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antepronotum with 4 setae. Dorsocentrals 17 partly biserial posterior, acrostichals 14, prealars 6. Scutellum with 13 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Wing</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
VR = 1.53. Brachiolum with 2 setae, R with 15 setae, R1 with 24 setae, R4+5 with 31 setae, remaining veins bare.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Spur of fore tibia 65 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long including 41 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long scale. Mid-tibia with 1 spur, 47 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long; hind tibia with 2 spurs, 43 and 65 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Combs of mid-tibia 29 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, of hind tibia 47 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Width at apex of fore tibia 69 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, of mid-tibia 73 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, of hind tibia 89 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Lengths and proportions of legs as in Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 6" captionStartId="T6" captionText="Table 6. Lengths (in μm) and proportions of leg segments in Nilothauma leccii sp. nov., adult male (n = 1)." pageId="0" pageNumber="81">6</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
